it-outline","\u002Fdocs\u002Fweb\u002Ftiptap","1.docs\u002Fweb\u002Ftiptap",[504],{"title":505,"path":506,"stem":507},"Snippets","\u002Fdocs\u002Fweb\u002Ftiptap\u002Fsnippets","1.docs\u002Fweb\u002Ftiptap\u002Fsnippets",{"id":509,"title":510,"authors":511,"badge":517,"body":518,"date":866,"description":867,"extension":868,"image":869,"meta":870,"navigation":875,"path":876,"seo":877,"stem":878,"__hash__":879},"posts\u002F3.blog\u002F2018\u002Fmy-new-home-office-setup.md","My New Home Office Setup",[512],{"name":513,"to":514,"avatar":515},"Alexander Trost","https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fgalexrt",{"src":516},"\u002Fimages\u002Fprofile-picture.jpg",null,{"type":519,"value":520,"toc":848},"minimark",[521,525,530,533,536,540,545,548,570,573,582,586,589,592,615,618,622,625,628,632,645,648,684,687,691,700,709,712,715,732,736,739,783,786,790,799,802,806,815,819,822,829,835,838,842,845],[522,523,524],"p",{},"In this post I'm going over my new game and home office setup.",[526,527,529],"h2",{"id":528},"new-table","New table",[522,531,532],{},"First part of the new home setup, was a new table.\nThe previous was a cheap table from IKEA. The new table is 2.60m long instead of previously only 2.00m.\nThe 0.60m more space is awesome. The desk feels emptier but in a good way, and I have more space for equipment.",[522,534,535],{},"If you have the space, go for a big table and keep it clean!",[526,537,539],{"id":538},"tech-stuff","Tech stuff",[541,542,544],"h3",{"id":543},"power-distribution","Power Distribution",[522,546,547],{},"The following power strips are used for power distribution:",[549,550,551,562],"ul",{},[552,553,554,555],"li",{},"2x ",[556,557,561],"a",{"href":558,"rel":559},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fintl\u002Fadam_hall_874716_power_strip_1_u_19.htm",[560],"nofollow","Adam Hall 874716 Power Strip 1 U 19\" - 16-port",[552,563,564,565],{},"And some ",[556,566,569],{"href":567,"rel":568},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fintl\u002Fthe_t_racks_power_8_s.htm",[560],"the t.racks Power 8 S - 8-port",[522,571,572],{},"The 16-port power strips are pretyy neat and I can recommend them.\n(I'll soon \"mount\" them to the table so that the cables are off the ground)",[522,574,575,576,581],{},"End goal here would be to finally buy myself a fancy ",[556,577,580],{"href":578,"rel":579},"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FUninterruptible_power_supply",[560],"Uninterruptible power supply",", just in case the apocalypse is happening :-D",[541,583,585],{"id":584},"network","Network",[522,587,588],{},"I'm driving a dual WAN setup using a FritzBoxes and a OpenSense firewall router.",[522,590,591],{},"OpenSense firewall router box hardware specifications:",[549,593,594,597,600,603,606,609,612],{},[552,595,596],{},"CPU: Intel Celeron G4900",[552,598,599],{},"Fan: Noctua NH-L9x65 CPU-Kühler",[552,601,602],{},"RAM: Crucial Ballistix DDR4-2666 4GB",[552,604,605],{},"Mainboard: Gigabyte B360N WIFI",[552,607,608],{},"PSU: Kolink SFX-350",[552,610,611],{},"Sorage: Samsung 860 EVO 260GB SSD",[552,613,614],{},"Case: Kolink - Satellite Mini-ITX-\u002F Micro-ATX-Gehäuse - schwarz",[522,616,617],{},"For network switches, I'm using two cheap 8-port Netgear Managed Switches which get the job done (they can VLAN so perfect with my OpenSense firewall router).",[541,619,621],{"id":620},"automation","Automation",[522,623,624],{},"I have a few Raspberry Pis which power the video surveillance and security system, and take care of home automations, like turning on the lights in the morning and so on.",[522,626,627],{},"I can probably extend this, but I'm fine with what it does right now.",[541,629,631],{"id":630},"computers","Computers",[633,634,635,642],"blockquote",{},[522,636,637,638,641],{},"The most important part of the calculation are the ",[639,640,630],"del",{}," calculators.",[522,643,644],{},"- Alexander Trost",[522,646,647],{},"I have two machines, one for gaming and one for working:",[549,649,650,667],{},[552,651,652,653],{},"Gaming\n",[549,654,655,658,661,664],{},[552,656,657],{},"CPU: Intel(c) I7-7700k",[552,659,660],{},"Memory: 16GB DDR4-3000",[552,662,663],{},"GPU: Nvidia GeForce GTX 970",[552,665,666],{},"Disk(s): 1x 500GB SATA SSD, 1x 3TB SATA HDD, 1x 4TB SATA HDD",[552,668,669,670],{},"Workstation\n",[549,671,672,675,678,681],{},[552,673,674],{},"CPU: AMD Ryzen 7 1800X",[552,676,677],{},"Memory: 32GB DDR4-2133",[552,679,680],{},"GPU: 2x Radeon RX 560 OC 4G",[552,682,683],{},"Disk(s): 1x 500GB NVMe SSD, 1x 500GB SATA SSD",[522,685,686],{},"Obviously the gaming computer can always need an upgrade but I am happy with it and the workstation.\nYou really notice the 8 cores and 16 threads of the AMD Ryzen when compiling code.",[541,688,690],{"id":689},"monitors","Monitors",[522,692,693,694,699],{},"I'm currently using 4x LG 29UM68-P 29\" 21:9 UltraWide LED monitors, see ",[556,695,698],{"href":696,"rel":697},"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.lg.com\u002Fus\u002Fmonitors\u002Flg-29UM68-P-ultrawide-monitor",[560],"LG 29UM68-P 29\" product page",".",[522,701,702,703,708],{},"A big shoutout to ",[556,704,707],{"href":705,"rel":706},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ricoo.eu\u002F",[560],"Ricoo Medientechnik"," for their awesome and not too expensive* monitor stands!",[522,710,711],{},"(*In comparsion with around 4 other companies that sell and\u002F or buy monitor stands)",[522,713,714],{},"I'm using the following monitor stands from Ricoo:",[549,716,717,725],{},[552,718,719,720],{},"1x ",[556,721,724],{"href":722,"rel":723},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ricoo.eu\u002Fen\u002Fricoo-pc-screen-led-monitor-stand-ts3511-table-mount-for-2-monitors-monitor-brackets-tft-swivel-arm-monitor-mount-pivoting-monitor-fastener-monitor-rack-monitor-arm-compatible-with-vesa-100x100\u002Fa-11189\u002F",[560],"Ricoo Monitor Stand TS3511 Table Mount for 2 Monitors (TS3011)",[552,726,554,727],{},[556,728,731],{"href":729,"rel":730},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.ricoo.eu\u002Fen\u002Fricoo-desk-mount-monitor-ts3011-with-gas-spring-articulation-monitor-bracket-swivelling-tiltable-desk-monitor-stand-pedestal-flat-screen-pc-monitor-tft-display-swivel-arm-desk-led-lcd-desk-holder-brackets-universal-tv-vesa-75x75-100x100\u002Fa-10789\u002F",[560],"Ricoo Desk Monitor Mount Arm (TS3011)",[541,733,735],{"id":734},"audio","Audio",[522,737,738],{},"Moving on to the audio equipment, I use the following pieces for audio input and output control:",[549,740,741,755,762,775],{},[552,742,743,748,749,754],{},[556,744,747],{"href":745,"rel":746},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fde\u002Fdbx_286_s.htm",[560],"DBX 286 S"," (Temporarily switched out for ",[556,750,753],{"href":751,"rel":752},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fgb\u002Fbehringer_xenyx_802.htm",[560],"Behringer 802 Xenyx",")",[552,756,757],{},[556,758,761],{"href":759,"rel":760},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fde\u002Frode_nt1a_complete_vocal_recording.htm",[560],"Rode NT1-A Complete Vocal Recording",[552,763,764,769,770,754],{},[556,765,768],{"href":766,"rel":767},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.thomann.de\u002Fgb\u002Fnumark_m_4_black.htm",[560],"Numark M 4"," (The link is to the black edition, but I have the grey one. I got it cheap from ",[556,771,774],{"href":772,"rel":773},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.rockshop.de\u002F",[560],"Rockshop.de",[552,776,777,782],{},[556,778,781],{"href":779,"rel":780},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.rockshop.de\u002Fakai-mpx8",[560],"Akai MPX8"," (Just for the lolz as a soundboard style \"player\")",[522,784,785],{},"To \"blast\" music at the neighbors I have a very old 5.1 sound system, which sadly has a high level of noise by default. I'll probably replace it soon with a better sound system.",[541,787,789],{"id":788},"chair","Chair",[522,791,792,793,798],{},"A ",[556,794,797],{"href":795,"rel":796},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.caseking.de\u002Fnoblechairs-epic-gaming-stuhl-schwarz-gold-gagc-038.html",[560],"noblechairs EPIC Gaming Stuhl - schwarz\u002Fgold"," because your arse and back will thank you for it.",[522,800,801],{},"Pretty good chair, though if you want to spend more go for a more expensive one with, e.g., \"limitless\" backrest and more features.",[526,803,805],{"id":804},"finishing-touches","Finishing touches",[522,807,808,809,814],{},"To give the whole setup a nice touch, I have added ",[556,810,813],{"href":811,"rel":812},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.amazon.de\u002FPhilips-LightStrip-erweiterbar-Millionen-kompatibel\u002Fdp\u002FB0148NMVQA",[560],"Philipps Hue LED Lightstrips"," to the back of the monitors. Though I still have to finally use the \"in-built\" glue of the light strips to put them on the back of the monitors.",[526,816,818],{"id":817},"result","Result",[522,820,821],{},"The result is pretty rad!",[522,823,824],{},[825,826],"img",{"alt":827,"src":828},"My New Home Setup - Rad Results!","\u002Fblog\u002F2018\u002Fmy-new-home-office-setup\u002Fhomeoffice-desktop-setup-shot-1.jpg",[522,830,831],{},[825,832],{"alt":833,"src":834},"My New Home Setup - With colored background lighting even better!","\u002Fblog\u002F2018\u002Fmy-new-home-office-setup\u002Fhomeoffice-desktop-setup-shot-2.jpg",[522,836,837],{},"(The LightStrip is hanging down as this was a picture during me gluing it to the monitors with the integrated glue strips)",[526,839,841],{"id":840},"summary","Summary",[522,843,844],{},"That is my home office setup. It gets the job done and is a dream come true for me.\nI have more ideas to exapnd this setup, e.g., making cut outs for the mixer, but I have to see if I'm going that far.",[522,846,847],{},"Have Fun!",{"title":849,"searchDepth":850,"depth":850,"links":851},"",2,[852,853,863,864,865],{"id":528,"depth":850,"text":529},{"id":538,"depth":850,"text":539,"children":854},[855,857,858,859,860,861,862],{"id":543,"depth":856,"text":544},3,{"id":584,"depth":856,"text":585},{"id":620,"depth":856,"text":621},{"id":630,"depth":856,"text":631},{"id":689,"depth":856,"text":690},{"id":734,"depth":856,"text":735},{"id":788,"depth":856,"text":789},{"id":804,"depth":850,"text":805},{"id":817,"depth":850,"text":818},{"id":840,"depth":850,"text":841},"2018-06-05T13:47:13+02:00","In this post I'm showing you my new gaming and home office setup.","md",{"src":828},{"tags":871},[872,873,874,631],"Home","Office","Setup",true,"\u002Fblog\u002F2018\u002Fmy-new-home-office-setup",{"title":510,"description":867},"3.blog\u002F2018\u002Fmy-new-home-office-setup","hwNBepAz0MnvdLeih_i8rzrhYZRvileshTW6GpZbcO4",[881,886],{"title":882,"path":883,"stem":884,"description":885,"children":-1},"KubeCon Copenhagen 2018 - Day 3","\u002Fblog\u002F2018\u002Fkubecon-copenhagen-2018-day-3","3.blog\u002F2018\u002Fkubecon-copenhagen-2018-day-3","Talks, keynotes, thoughts and pictures from the KubeCon Copenhagen 2018 Day 3.",{"title":887,"path":888,"stem":889,"description":890,"children":-1},"What exactly is „Cloud Native\" even?","\u002Fblog\u002F2018\u002Fwhat-exactly-is-cloud-native-even","3.blog\u002F2018\u002Fwhat-exactly-is-cloud-native-even","Cross-Post of my \"What exactly is „Cloud Native\" even?\" article from \"The Cloud Report\"",1777401722609]